The `\tableofcontents` command generates the TOC. LaTeX automatically creates the TOC by scanning the document for sectional units (sections, subsections, etc.) and creating a list of them.

Here is the resulting TOC:

Introduction ....................................................... 1
Methods ......................................................... 2
   Method 1 ............................................... 2
Results ....................................................... 3
   Result 1 ............................................... 3

You can customize the appearance of the TOC by using various options and packages. For example, you can change the font, spacing, and layout of the TOC using the `tocstyle` package.

Here is an example with customizations:
```
\documentclass{article}
